rComments: One of the best profs Ive ever had! Hes well spoken in a relatable way. Hes clear and up to date; he knows what students will relate to. He makes sure he gets through to you, and always asks for your opinion. Hes extremely passionate about his work. His lectures are the kind you dont want to skip or else you might miss something awesome.

there are a ton of readings but they're diverse and interesting. prof johnson is extremely passionate about the material so lectures were interesting. he also genuinely cares about the opinions and well being of his students. HIS222 is one of those courses in uni that changes you - you definitely come out a better person and historian.

Mr. Johnson is such an amazing, caring Prof. You can tell he's so passionate about the course material. Make use of his office hours as he is a fountain of knowledge! I had a really rough year at U of T and he made it worthwhile. Thank you Sir! Make sure you attend all lectures and tutorials, as those are a big part of the mark.

Professor Johnson is an incredible addition to the History department. Do your readings!!! a lot of primary source texts & great variety of content. I would def recommend the course! Great professor if ur looking to improve your writing or get to know a faculty member. He knows a lot, so sometimes lectures can have tangents, learn from them!

Chris is super passionate and down to earth. He's the kind of professor who 100% treats you more as a peer than a student. His lectures are really interesting and he leaves lots of room for discussion. The only downside is that sometimes he gets a little behind the syllabus so you might not know what week's readings he'll quiz you on. He's amazing!
